Awesome — here’s a clean, production-grade way to build the Notification API request with a dynamic placeholders bag and a simple call from your run method.

The design is:
	•	POJOs: NotificationRequest, Recipient, Agency
	•	Builder: NotificationPayloadBuilder (stateless, thread-safe)
	•	Serialization: Jackson ObjectMapper
	•	Dynamic placeholders: either pass a Map<String,Object> in the context under placeholders, or prefix any context keys with ph. (e.g. ph.contractDate) and they’ll be auto-collected.

