How to call it from your run method

Right after your allowed-agency check succeeds, build the payload and serialize it. (You’ll enqueue it later.)

// inside your ServiceBusProcessorFunction.run(...)
try {
    // ... after parsing, lookups, and allow-list checks

    Map<String,Object> ctx = recipientMapFromCosmosDb;  // your context produced by LookupExecutor
    // You can also enrich ctx here if needed:
    // ctx.put("recipient.email", someValueFromLookups);
    // ctx.put("ph.contractDate", "2025-08-24"); // auto-collected into placeholders

    var req = NotificationPayloadBuilder.build(
            ctx,
            parsedMessage.getNotify().getNotificationType(),  // notificationType
            parsedMessage.getNotify().getTriggerType(),       // triggerType
            "email",                                          // messageType (decide per channel)
            "ja",                                             // language (from context or rules)
            strOrNull(parsedMessage.getKeys().get("applicationId")),
            strOrNull(parsedMessage.getKeys().get("policyId")),
            log
    );

    String json = NotificationPayloadBuilder.toJson(req);
    log.info("Notification JSON: " + json);

    // TODO next step: enqueue 'json' to your notification-request queue

} catch (Exception ex) {
    log.severe("Failed to build notification payload: " + ex.getMessage());
    throw new RuntimeException(ex); // let Functions retry / DLQ
}

// helper:
private static String strOrNull(Object o) { return o == null ? null : o.toString(); }


